sixmensmorris

Class Board

  • java.lang.Object
    • sixmensmorris.Board

  • public class Board
extends java.lang.Object
    This is an abstract representation of the game board. It keeps the state of each piece in a 1 dimensional array in order to reduce run time and space. Note that by using modular arithmetic, we can represent the the Board as a 1 dimensional array. Pieces are adjacent to pieces that are beside it in the array, and 8 spots ahead or behind it. This fact can be used in order to determine which pieces to check to determine a victory condition in the future, as well as where a certain piece can move in the gameplay state.
    Version:
    1
    Author:
    Kelvin Lin, Jeremy Klotz
